  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-9 low confidence, honestly documented)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Evidence carries explicitly low confidence (~50%) due to limited experimental replicates and wide turbulence-model uncertainty bounds; these limitations are documented honestly with full rationale. The assessment team accepted the model with residual uncertainty acknowledged and sensitivity analysis informing the decision.",
