    "name": "Global sensitivity analysis — uncertain inputs driving wide hemolysis bounds",
    "description": "Sobol first-order and total-effect indices computed over six uncertain inputs: turbulence model selection (accounts for 38% of NIH output variance), power-law coefficient C (29%), exponent α (18%), mesh resolution (8%), blood viscosity (5%), and inlet velocity profile shape (2%). Turbulence model choice and power-law coefficient C together explain 67% of the total output variance and are the primary drivers of the wide ±55% uncertainty bounds on the hemolysis index; these findings directly informed the decision to accept the model with explicit acknowledgement of residual turbulence-model uncertainty."
